    "updated_at": "2016-10-13T12:10:44Z",
    "body": "I'm not sure this is the source of the problem, but you can try to prevent Electron (in fact, Chromium) from throttling a background renderer, by:\n1. running Electron with the `--disable-renderer-backgrounding` [command-line switch](http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/chrome-command-line-switches/)\n2. initializing your [Browser Windows](http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/browser-window/) with `webPreferences.backgroundThrottling = false` \n3. Run the [silent audio hack](https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/9485/files) in your renderer processes (web pages).\n\nIn addition, you should be able to listen to the `crashed` event on your renderer process, and try to recover from the crash if possible, regardless of the source of the problem. \n\nAs for figuring out the source of the problem, anyone trying to help would need additional information, or a simplified test case.\n"
